Oven-Baked Salmon with Herbs

Rating: 4.6 stars

A foolproof oven-baked salmon dish that is easy to make and big on flavor. If you don't like dill, you could try other fresh herbs, or even a mixture of dill, parsley, and spring onion.

By Natalie Titanov

Oven-Baked Salmon with Herbs


    ,

    Directions

    Instructions Checklist

    • Combine dill, olive oil, lemon juice, honey, garlic, coriander, salt, and pepper in a small bowl.

      Advertisement

    • Rinse salmon fillet under running cold water and pat dry with paper towels. Lay salmon skin-side down on a large piece of plastic wrap. Spread dill mixture all over the top of the fish, wrap well with plastic wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

    • Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Unwrap salmon and place skin-side down in a baking dish.

    • Bake in the preheated oven until salmon flakes easily with a fork, 12 to 15 minutes.

    Nutrition Facts

    Per Serving:
    284 calories; protein 35.1g; carbohydrates 5.7g; fat 13.3g; cholesterol 81.1mg; sodium 115.5mg. Full Nutrition

    HEIDEL
    Rating: 4 stars
    03/21/2020
    Found this recipe while looking for something quick. I usually go for the highly rated recipes, but this looked so easy. It did not disappoint. Prep was a snap, let it sit, then throw in the oven. Full disclosure, I did NOT have fresh dill so used dry. It was flavorful with a hint of sweetness from the honey and an interesting coriander finish, (a spice I rarely use). I will definitely try this with fresh dill. I rarely rate recipes because I use highly rated ones most of the time. Thought I should do my duty here on this one as there were only 2 reviews and this really was good. Thanks for sharing!     Josie
    Rating: 5 stars
    07/24/2019
    Excellent!! Except! I baked it skin side up for 5 min. Peeled of skin. Then flipped entire salmon and continued to bake (on cookie sheet ) 15 more minutes. Amazing.
    Robert Boggs
    Rating: 4 stars
    04/16/2019
    I think I over cooked it...but it was still very good and even better as leftovers with salad the next day
    HEIDEL
    Rating: 4 stars
    03/21/2020
    Found this recipe while looking for something quick. I usually go for the highly rated recipes, but this looked so easy. It did not disappoint. Prep was a snap, let it sit, then throw in the oven. Full disclosure, I did NOT have fresh dill so used dry. It was flavorful with a hint of sweetness from the honey and an interesting coriander finish, (a spice I rarely use). I will definitely try this with fresh dill. I rarely rate recipes because I use highly rated ones most of the time. Thought I should do my duty here on this one as there were only 2 reviews and this really was good. Thanks for sharing!
